1
00:01:43,749 --> 00:01:46,630
Plagued by low approval ratings,
the Watanabe Cabinet is

2
00:01:46,713 --> 00:01:48,383
now facing a crisis.

3
00:01:49,678 --> 00:01:52,684
<i>The Democratic Constitutional Party</i>

4
00:01:52,767 --> 00:01:55,230
<i>submitted a motion of no confidence
yesterday,</i>

5
00:01:55,313 --> 00:01:58,946
<i>accusing the Watanabe Cabinet
of ignoring the opinions of its citizens.</i>

6
00:01:59,865 --> 00:02:03,329
<i>A no-confidence motion was expected
to be submitted during this session…</i>

7
00:02:03,413 --> 00:02:04,916
NO-CONFIDENCE MOTION SUBMITTED

8
00:02:05,000 --> 00:02:08,006
<i>…but the timing of it,
right before this weekend's final vote</i>

9
00:02:08,089 --> 00:02:10,761
<i>on the Global Bill,
has left many politicians stunned.</i>

10
00:02:12,765 --> 00:02:16,397
<i>The Prime Minister's Cabinet responded
with a detailed--</i>

11
00:02:18,318 --> 00:02:19,696
What are you thinking?

12
00:02:20,656 --> 00:02:22,660
There is something odd about this.

13
00:02:25,081 --> 00:02:30,300
The opposing camp would not do
something like this, unless…

14
00:02:32,346 --> 00:02:34,893
they made some sort of deal with someone.

15
00:02:35,561 --> 00:02:36,772
Is it Saijo?

16
00:02:36,855 --> 00:02:38,943
Don't jump to conclusions.

17
00:02:41,113 --> 00:02:47,836
However, something is happening
out of my sight.

18
00:02:49,046 --> 00:02:50,173
What should we do?

19
00:02:57,856 --> 00:03:01,237
I'll have a talk
with Secretary-General Takeuchi.

20
00:03:04,159 --> 00:03:06,999
Do you think he knew about this?

21
00:03:08,001 --> 00:03:09,420
He must have.

22
00:03:11,215 --> 00:03:12,301
However…

23
00:03:14,346 --> 00:03:16,935
he did not say a word to me.

24
00:03:20,860 --> 00:03:25,703
Prime Minister Watanabe will resign,
and the Global Bill will fail.

25
00:03:38,478 --> 00:03:39,939
I'm pregnant.

26
00:03:42,779 --> 00:03:43,989
I'm carrying your child.

27
00:03:47,830 --> 00:03:48,874
Really?

28
00:03:50,335 --> 00:03:51,838
I'm really happy.

29
00:03:57,850 --> 00:03:59,103
Really, really happy.

30
00:04:00,523 --> 00:04:01,733
Me too.

31
00:04:02,652 --> 00:04:04,948
I was afraid of what you'd say.

32
00:04:05,700 --> 00:04:07,537
-Why would you be?
-[chuckles]

33
00:04:08,706 --> 00:04:10,584
Doesn't it complicate things?

34
00:04:12,421 --> 00:04:13,423
I know it will.

35
00:04:14,509 --> 00:04:15,970
Actually, it's the opposite.

36
00:04:19,226 --> 00:04:21,815
Will you divorce your wife?

37
00:04:22,399 --> 00:04:23,401
Yeah.

38
00:04:24,028 --> 00:04:27,242
I don't love her. I'll get a divorce.

39
00:04:28,954 --> 00:04:32,127
Does that mean
we can get married right away?

40
00:04:33,463 --> 00:04:34,507
No.

41
00:04:38,264 --> 00:04:39,559
You're not ready to?

42
00:04:40,644 --> 00:04:41,646
I am.

43
00:04:43,399 --> 00:04:45,403
I just need to figure things out.

44
00:04:46,072 --> 00:04:50,581
[Nami] But you're scared because
you don't know how your family will react.

45
00:04:53,419 --> 00:04:55,215
What era are we living in?

46
00:04:56,843 --> 00:04:57,887
I know.

47
00:04:58,722 --> 00:05:00,643
I know in my head.

48
00:05:04,066 --> 00:05:09,243
I don't want this child to grow up
looking at a father he can't respect.

49
00:05:16,465 --> 00:05:18,052
What happened?

50
00:05:18,554 --> 00:05:21,685
Well… [chuckles]
…I'm not exactly sure myself.

51
00:05:22,352 --> 00:05:27,362
[Ogami] <i>You kept
the motion of no confidence a secret.</i>

52
00:05:27,445 --> 00:05:31,036
I never knew about it. Believe me.

53
00:05:32,540 --> 00:05:36,798
Are you telling me to believe
you weren't the one

54
00:05:37,382 --> 00:05:38,886
<i>who convinced them to submit it?</i>

55
00:05:38,969 --> 00:05:42,852
You must believe me.

56
00:05:44,062 --> 00:05:48,780
So, who will be the next prime minister?

57
00:05:49,281 --> 00:05:51,536
I can't say for certain.

58
00:05:52,162 --> 00:05:55,126
It's a complicated
and confusing situation.

59
00:05:56,378 --> 00:06:00,094
Prime Minister Watanabe has
lost her power,

60
00:06:00,178 --> 00:06:02,015
<i>and I cannot predict what will come next.</i>

61
00:06:02,892 --> 00:06:07,067
What will your faction do?

62
00:06:09,404 --> 00:06:11,367
Formally, they will

63
00:06:12,745 --> 00:06:14,331
vote for me.

64
00:06:15,375 --> 00:06:17,337
[Ogami laughs]

65
00:06:18,840 --> 00:06:20,844
Yes, they will.

66
00:06:21,972 --> 00:06:23,265
[chuckles]

67
00:06:41,678 --> 00:06:43,097
[door closes]

68
00:06:48,024 --> 00:06:51,030
[breathes deeply] Wow, that looks amazing.

69
00:06:52,950 --> 00:06:54,327
It was yesterday's dinner.

70
00:06:54,411 --> 00:06:55,413
[sighs]

71
00:06:55,998 --> 00:06:57,167
I'm so sorry.

72
00:06:59,379 --> 00:07:03,012
But, I really need to get
right back to work. Sorry.

73
00:07:04,389 --> 00:07:05,433
Work?

74
00:07:06,060 --> 00:07:07,437
Yeah.

75
00:07:07,521 --> 00:07:09,859
There's a lot going on.
It's an important time.

76
00:07:13,658 --> 00:07:15,161
I really need to go now.

77
00:07:16,831 --> 00:07:20,296
I really have a lot to think about
these days.

78
00:07:22,175 --> 00:07:24,806
But everything will be
finished by this weekend.

79
00:07:27,352 --> 00:07:28,437
Okay.

80
00:07:30,526 --> 00:07:32,153
[Kageyama] I'll get going now.

81
00:07:32,237 --> 00:07:33,615
Wait.

82
00:07:35,118 --> 00:07:36,328
What?

83
00:07:39,544 --> 00:07:40,712
Never mind.

84
00:07:42,006 --> 00:07:43,259
It's nothing.

85
00:07:43,844 --> 00:07:44,846
[sighs]

86
00:08:29,518 --> 00:08:31,731
On top of Maruyama's dumb antics,

87
00:08:31,814 --> 00:08:34,319
Saijo has been lurking around
like a hyena.

88
00:08:35,363 --> 00:08:37,283
There is no one I can trust anymore.

89
00:08:38,536 --> 00:08:41,416
-[sighs]
-[Ogami] Was it Secretary-General Takeuchi

90
00:08:41,500 --> 00:08:46,678
who gave the opposing party the suggestion
to submit the motion of no confidence?

91
00:08:47,178 --> 00:08:48,305
I don't know.

92
00:08:49,432 --> 00:08:52,146
Saijo could have made a deal with them.

93
00:08:54,527 --> 00:08:58,242
Isn't this the first time
you were completely in the dark?

94
00:08:59,327 --> 00:09:01,373
This is not a problem with me,

95
00:09:02,585 --> 00:09:04,170
but with you.

96
00:09:04,714 --> 00:09:06,383
Do you really think so?

97
00:09:07,761 --> 00:09:11,268
Aren't you jumping to conclusions?

98
00:09:13,606 --> 00:09:16,738
You should take the time
to look in the mirror.

99
00:09:17,531 --> 00:09:18,533
And you?

100
00:09:19,577 --> 00:09:20,579
Me?

101
00:09:21,455 --> 00:09:22,457
I always do

102
00:09:23,167 --> 00:09:26,549
what I think is right.

103
00:09:36,694 --> 00:09:38,405
[clicks tongue, sighs]

104
00:09:40,076 --> 00:09:44,669
So, how much trust can you give Takeuchi?

105
00:09:45,378 --> 00:09:47,090
Why ask now?

106
00:09:48,300 --> 00:09:50,847
I'm thinking about who would
benefit the most from this.

107
00:09:56,233 --> 00:09:57,235
[sighs]

108
00:10:09,259 --> 00:10:11,471
Listen. It all depends on you.

109
00:10:13,225 --> 00:10:14,352
On me?

110
00:10:15,146 --> 00:10:16,231
What do you mean?

111
00:10:17,943 --> 00:10:20,239
In any case, you think I'm the problem.

112
00:10:20,322 --> 00:10:25,542
That's why… [whispering]
…that man created a way out for you.

113
00:10:27,546 --> 00:10:30,301
Not for me. For you.

114
00:10:33,348 --> 00:10:37,356
Hey, this is a problem you made.

115
00:10:37,440 --> 00:10:39,570
Partying with women at your age.

116
00:10:39,653 --> 00:10:41,323
Not thinking about your position.

117
00:10:41,406 --> 00:10:43,828
What else would it be but reckless?

118
00:10:44,580 --> 00:10:47,794
This would never have happened
if you weren't so stupid.

119
00:10:49,715 --> 00:10:50,759
[Masashi sighs]

120
00:10:52,554 --> 00:10:54,432
It's not like I'm always partying.

121
00:10:55,685 --> 00:10:58,566
Everyone has to let loose sometimes.

122
00:11:01,363 --> 00:11:02,658
And you say I'm stupid?

123
00:11:04,077 --> 00:11:05,622
Then what about you?

124
00:11:06,582 --> 00:11:10,966
Look in my eyes and say
your integrity is spotless.

125
00:11:11,049 --> 00:11:12,719
[skateboard clatters, echoes]

126
00:11:15,432 --> 00:11:18,815
You'll vote just as that man told you to.

127
00:11:20,442 --> 00:11:23,575
Your first election was a scam.

128
00:11:25,369 --> 00:11:28,000
But the world will never know
anything, will it?

129
00:11:29,043 --> 00:11:34,304
Except that Hiroshi Maruyama's brother
went to jail for assaulting a hostess.

130
00:11:40,190 --> 00:11:41,318
[child, in English] Wait for me.

131
00:11:41,401 --> 00:11:43,030
-[child 2] Hey!
-[child 3] Loser.

132
00:11:43,113 --> 00:11:44,365
[child 1] No. No.

133
00:11:46,746 --> 00:11:48,791
[speaking indistinctly]

134
00:11:51,839 --> 00:11:53,760
Hey, do you have business with that guy?

135
00:11:53,843 --> 00:11:56,222
-Uh, yeah, we're just--
-Oh, okay.

136
00:11:56,724 --> 00:11:58,143
[child 1, child 2] Hey.

137
00:11:58,226 --> 00:11:59,688
[child 3] Three, two, one.

138
00:11:59,772 --> 00:12:02,026
-[children exclaiming]
-[Murata] Shut up!

139
00:12:02,109 --> 00:12:04,865
[children jeering, chattering]

140
00:12:04,949 --> 00:12:07,411
-Run. Run, run.
-[laughing]

141
00:12:08,205 --> 00:12:09,248
Trust me.

142
00:12:11,629 --> 00:12:15,679
[Murata] You guys better leave me alone or
I'm gonna go out there and kick your ass!

143
00:12:16,179 --> 00:12:17,473
[gasps]

144
00:12:17,557 --> 00:12:19,394
-Hey.
-Sarah?

145
00:12:19,477 --> 00:12:21,231
-Can we talk?
-[sighs]

146
00:12:22,358 --> 00:12:23,485
Who is that?

147
00:12:25,280 --> 00:12:26,826
[Sarah] This is Ryu Ogami.

148
00:12:26,909 --> 00:12:28,663
-[scoffs]
-Oh, Max. Come on.

149
00:12:28,746 --> 00:12:31,544
[Murata] You brought an Ogami
to my office?

150
00:12:31,627 --> 00:12:33,005
[Sarah] He's a friend.

151
00:12:33,965 --> 00:12:36,512
-Max, please. This is important.
-[Murata sighs]

152
00:12:37,471 --> 00:12:38,766
This is so fucked up.

153
00:12:39,977 --> 00:12:42,816
You both are fucked up.
I mean, we're all fucked up.

154
00:12:43,818 --> 00:12:46,197
-That's right.
-Show me more a bit more excitement?

155
00:12:49,580 --> 00:12:51,959
[Murata] Mmm. Mmm!

156
00:12:52,961 --> 00:12:55,299
[grunts] You guys are something.

157
00:12:55,800 --> 00:12:57,094
It's not gonna end well for you.

158
00:12:57,596 --> 00:13:01,019
Double homicide.
Double suicide for you two. You know?

159
00:13:01,604 --> 00:13:05,194
I'm just joking, but, you know,
just you guys dating says something.

160
00:13:05,862 --> 00:13:07,156
Does your dad know?

161
00:13:07,741 --> 00:13:08,743
Yeah.

162
00:13:09,285 --> 00:13:10,287
[Murata] Wow.

163
00:13:10,997 --> 00:13:12,751
-And you guys are still dating?
-Okay.

164
00:13:12,834 --> 00:13:15,632
-And you're still alive? [laughs]
-[Sarah] Not important.

165
00:13:17,468 --> 00:13:20,057
You guys are dating.
Okay, well, you should have some.

166
00:13:20,558 --> 00:13:21,811
All yours.

167
00:13:23,105 --> 00:13:25,902
These are the best burgers
since Georgetown.

168
00:13:26,486 --> 00:13:27,614
So you went to Georgetown?

169
00:13:28,240 --> 00:13:30,787
Yeah, why? What else do you know about me?

170
00:13:30,870 --> 00:13:33,375
Okay, calm down.
We all have the same goal.

171
00:13:33,918 --> 00:13:35,672
Bring down the government?

172
00:13:35,755 --> 00:13:38,845
No. To get to the truth.

173
00:13:40,264 --> 00:13:41,266
[Murata] Hmm.

174
00:13:44,063 --> 00:13:45,107
Okay.

175
00:13:45,817 --> 00:13:46,902
What do you wanna know?

176
00:13:47,571 --> 00:13:49,323
Manabu Takeuchi.

177
00:13:49,407 --> 00:13:53,081
All I know about that Manabu--
That thing stunk so bad.

178
00:13:53,875 --> 00:13:57,799
It was like all the fish of Tsukiji's fish
going bad all at once.

179
00:14:00,387 --> 00:14:02,726
Then the guy arrested gets whacked?

180
00:14:03,435 --> 00:14:06,316
What, he committed suicide?
That's bullshit, man.

181
00:14:07,234 --> 00:14:08,654
That guy got whacked.

182
00:14:09,238 --> 00:14:10,240
You have evidence?

183
00:14:10,324 --> 00:14:12,954
Evidence? Did you just get off the plane?

184
00:14:13,038 --> 00:14:15,877
You're in Japan.
There is no evidence here.

185
00:14:15,960 --> 00:14:18,423
Ninety-nine percent conviction rate.

186
00:14:18,507 --> 00:14:21,220
They don't even present evidence in court.

187
00:14:21,304 --> 00:14:22,849
All they get is confessions.

188
00:14:23,893 --> 00:14:25,228
Hey, we think you did it.

189
00:14:25,312 --> 00:14:29,195
Now, put your John Hancock here,
and everything is solved.

190
00:14:29,780 --> 00:14:33,871
Everyone, everyone, everyone
gets to save time and money,

191
00:14:33,955 --> 00:14:36,585
crime rates are low,
everybody looks the other way,

192
00:14:37,252 --> 00:14:38,380
and life goes on.

193
00:14:39,006 --> 00:14:40,635
Okay, can we go back to Manabu?

194
00:14:42,847 --> 00:14:44,768
What do you know about Five Winds?

195
00:14:44,851 --> 00:14:47,398
[Murata] What's that?
Should I know something?

196
00:14:47,481 --> 00:14:50,989
Five Winds is a company that was
registered under Manabu Takeuchi.

197
00:14:51,072 --> 00:14:52,074
[Murata] Yeah, so?

198
00:14:53,326 --> 00:14:54,913
Doesn't exist.

199
00:14:54,997 --> 00:14:56,332
We went to the offices.

200
00:14:56,416 --> 00:14:58,921
There was nothing there, didn't exist.
Just a sign on the front door.

201
00:14:59,005 --> 00:15:00,007
Nothing else.

202
00:15:00,842 --> 00:15:05,183
And my NPO has been sending money to Five
Winds, a company that doesn't even exist.

203
00:15:06,102 --> 00:15:10,027
Oh, so Manabu and Takeuchi set up
a company, and there's no company.

204
00:15:10,945 --> 00:15:15,747
And a governmental NPO sends money
to a nonexistent company.

205
00:15:15,830 --> 00:15:18,001
And then Manabu gets killed
in a bar fight,

206
00:15:18,084 --> 00:15:19,755
and the murder suspect commits suicide.

207
00:15:20,464 --> 00:15:23,637
So, someone had Manabu killed,
and to cover it up,

208
00:15:24,514 --> 00:15:26,309
someone had the suspect killed.

209
00:15:26,392 --> 00:15:28,814
But there's no way somebody's gonna
get killed in a bar fight.

210
00:15:29,524 --> 00:15:31,402
Or commit suicide in fucking prison.

211
00:15:31,904 --> 00:15:33,824
You think it's something
to do with the drugs?

212
00:15:34,576 --> 00:15:36,789
Rumor was Manabu was
involved with a drug trade.

213
00:15:37,372 --> 00:15:38,918
Drugs? Manabu?

214
00:15:39,503 --> 00:15:42,007
I mean he partied hard and, generally,
he was an asshole,

215
00:15:42,091 --> 00:15:43,594
but he stayed away from drugs.

216
00:15:44,345 --> 00:15:46,224
No, no, no. Manabu? No way.

217
00:15:46,307 --> 00:15:48,144
[inhales deeply]

218
00:15:49,063 --> 00:15:50,775
So, Manabu didn't do drugs?

219
00:15:51,275 --> 00:15:52,444
[Murata] No, he didn't.

220
00:15:54,574 --> 00:15:58,206
There are rumors that they swept
Manabu's drug use under the rug…

221
00:15:58,289 --> 00:16:01,212
[inhales sharply]
…to protect Takeuchi's reputation.

222
00:16:02,256 --> 00:16:05,638
Who's they? Takeuchi and your father?

223
00:16:08,184 --> 00:16:11,984
So, Takeuchi asked your father to fix
Manabu's drug issues.

224
00:16:12,694 --> 00:16:14,739
And Manabu doesn't even do drugs.

225
00:16:17,912 --> 00:16:19,875
Holy shit.

226
00:16:20,585 --> 00:16:21,587
[Sarah] What?

227
00:16:31,480 --> 00:16:33,736
Takeuchi had his son whacked.

228
00:16:36,909 --> 00:16:39,998
He had his own fucking son whacked.

229
