Manabu was gonna blow the whistle
on the Five Winds slush fund.

230
00:16:50,435 --> 00:16:51,897
Takeuchi whacked him.

231
00:16:53,567 --> 00:16:55,070
In order to cover it up,

232
00:16:55,988 --> 00:16:58,451
he killed some poor bystander.

233
00:17:01,917 --> 00:17:03,336
And your father

234
00:17:04,839 --> 00:17:06,175
helped him get away with it all.

235
00:17:08,764 --> 00:17:11,603
Mmm… [chewing] …these are really good.

236
00:17:11,687 --> 00:17:13,231
You guys sure you don't want any?

237
00:17:22,040 --> 00:17:25,463
[person, in Japanese] Did you read
the e-mail I sent the other day?

238
00:17:25,548 --> 00:17:28,512
[person 2] Yes, well…

239
00:17:35,693 --> 00:17:36,903
Hello.

240
00:17:41,997 --> 00:17:43,291
This is Mr. Nakagawa.

241
00:17:44,251 --> 00:17:47,341
He's the head of the investment strategy
department that manages prop trading.

242
00:17:47,884 --> 00:17:49,094
Nice to meet you.

243
00:17:49,846 --> 00:17:52,602
Nice to meet you. I'm Yumiko Kageyama.

244
00:17:53,394 --> 00:17:56,735
You were working here
until you got married?

245
00:17:56,818 --> 00:17:59,783
Yes, that was ten years ago.

246
00:17:59,866 --> 00:18:03,081
As I've reported, she was
a very talented colleague.

247
00:18:03,666 --> 00:18:07,757
I've had a hard time hiring
new, young employees who can work hard.

248
00:18:07,840 --> 00:18:09,385
Especially women.

249
00:18:09,468 --> 00:18:10,930
Is that so?

250
00:18:11,890 --> 00:18:15,940
My department needs to
aggressively hire more women.

251
00:18:16,440 --> 00:18:19,739
After all, it is a part
of the company's strategy.

252
00:18:20,866 --> 00:18:23,706
It's part of the CEO's
business reformation plan.

253
00:18:26,419 --> 00:18:31,429
I was told this company made approximately
1.2 billion yen in profits last year.

254
